window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>The Mossad is widely recognized today as the best intelligence service in the world. It is also the most enigmatic, shrouded in secrecy. In <i>Mossad</i>, authors MichaelBar-Zohar and Nissim Mishal take us behind the closed curtain with riveting, eye-opening, boots-on-the-ground accounts of the most dangerous, most crucial missions in the agency's 60-year history. These are real <i>Mission: Impossible</i> true stories brimming with high-octane action - from the breathtaking capture of Nazi executioner Adolf Eichmann to the recent elimination of key Iranian nuclear scientists. </p> <p>Anyone who is fascinated by the world of international espionage, intelligence, and covert black-ops warfare will find <i>Mossad</i> electrifying.</p>"; 
